By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission(EFCC) has arrested the erstwhile governor of Imo State, Rochas Okorocha, his wife, Nkechi Okorocha and two others. According to Daily Trust, the anti-corruption commission arrested Okorocha, barely 24 hours after leaving office was arrested along side Gerald Okorocha and Okey Okorocha. The commission also sealed his Eastern Palm University, Ogboko. Details later….  